      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Framing rapid developers as merely \"reckless\" is an oversimplification, as they genuinely believe they are leading a necessary technological revolution. Accelerationists argue that the benefits of advanced AI—like curing diseases or solving climate change—are so immense that delaying development for fear of hypothetical risks is itself a moral failure. They view regulation as a brake on human progress, insisting that the pace of innovation must be prioritized to achieve massive societal gains.",
